The paper deals with the problem of communication with feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). However, the authors approach the problem from a control-theoretic perspective, mapping the communication problem to a control problem, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses code design, which is a topic in networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses a linear quadratic Gaussian control problem to obtain a sum rate optimal code for the N-sender AWGN multiple access channel, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
